<taxonomicName authority="Mahunka, 1986" authorityName="Mahunka" authorityYear="1986" class="Arachnida" family="Carabodidae" genus="Berndobodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="13" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Berndobodes</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="13" pageNumber="86" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="86">
Subfamily: 
<taxonomicName pageId="13" pageNumber="86" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Bernodobodinae">Bernodobodinae</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="13" pageNumber="86" rank="subFamily">subfam. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="86">Prodorsum: Lamellae with a sharp outer cuspis, lamellar setae arising on them. Prelamellae - like costulae - present, which continue from the inner side of lamellae. Rostral setae arising before the lamellar ones. Prodorsum with one pair of protuberances, interlamellar setae originating on them. Sensillus long, with slightly dilated head. Tutorium well developed.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="86">Notogaster: Dorsosejugal region normal, dorsosejugal suture present. Fifteen pairs of spathulate notogastral setae, one of them arising on the large humeral apophysis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="86">
Coxisternal region: Apodemes and borders weakly developed, epimeres partly opened. Epimeral setal formula: 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="—1—3—" pageId="13" pageNumber="86">-1-3-</normalizedToken>
3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="86">
Anogenital region: Anogenital setal formula: 4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="—1—2—" pageId="13" pageNumber="86">-1-2-</normalizedToken>
3. Lyrifissure iad removed very far from the anal aperture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="86" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="86">
Type species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Mahunka, 1986" authorityName="Mahunka" authorityYear="1986" class="Arachnida" family="Carabodidae" genus="Berndobodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="13" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spathulifer">Berndobodes spathulifer</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="13" pageNumber="86" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
** Sabah (Malaysia).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="86">** The description is given later.</paragraph>
